"Manual pull requests": Each PR corresponds to
updating one page of content. For each PR, Netlify
generates a deploy-preview and updates that preview
as the PR is modified by additional commits. That
preview and its corresponding thread of PR-
comments is the basis of all discussion about updates
to that page.
These are similar to manual PRs except that Netlify CMS
names and manages them automatically.
Each page has a status that corresponds to a GitHub label
associated with the PR (e.g., netlify-cms/draft).
Changes to website infrastructure are
managed on different branches than changes
to page content. Each infrastructure branch
corresponds to a "release" of the website.
Most team members contribute only to
changes in page content. Bruce and any
other website builders would also contribute
to changes in website infrastructure.
